article.headline: New Hampshire 63, Richmond 49
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- Mike Skrocki scored 18 points and Reggie Brown added 12, all in the second half, as Richmond beat New Hampshire 63-49 on Tuesday night to advance to the semifinals of the Guardians Classic. The Spiders (2-0) withstood seven 3-pointers by New Hampshire's Marcus Bullock, the last two capping a 13-5 run that pulled the Wildcats to 52-48 with 5:38 remaining. Richmond was scoreless for nearly four minutes during the run. But the Wildcats got no closer, as Brown hit a fastbreak layup with 4:20 to play and New Hampshire (1-1) missed three of four free throws in the waning minutes. Brown, who missed all of last season with a back injury, hit two 3-pointers, a pullup jumper and a layup over a 5-minute span early in the second half as the Spiders opened a 50-38 lead. He finished 5-for-12 from the field, 2-for-7 on 3-pointers. Tony Dobbins added 12 points, nine rebounds and six assists for the Spiders. New Hampshire had 11 turnovers in the first half, but the Wildcats stayed close at 30-24 by shooting 50 percent from the field. The Spiders will next travel to Kansas City, Mo., for the semifinals of the tournament, which is using experimental rule changes including a trapezoid lane and extended 3-point line.
